# IKO – Gamified Life Reminder App

Build a mobile application called "IKO" that transforms real-life tasks and habits into a role-playing game (RPG).

## Core Idea

Users create real-life tasks such as:

* Go to the gym
* Study for 2 hours
* Drink water
* Read a book
* Clean the room
* Sleep before 11 PM

Instead of simple reminders, these tasks become "Quests".

When users complete quests, they earn:

* Experience Points (XP)
* Coins
* Achievement Badges
* Streak Bonuses
* Character Progression

The goal is to make productivity feel like playing a game.

## Main Features

### 1. User Profile

* Username
* Avatar
* Level
* XP Bar
* Coin Balance
* Current Streak
* Total Quests Completed

### 2. Quest System

Users can:

* Create quests
* Edit quests
* Delete quests
* Mark quests as completed

Each quest contains:

* Title
* Description
* Difficulty (Easy, Medium, Hard)
* XP Reward
* Coin Reward
* Due Time
* Repeat Schedule

### 3. Reminder System

* Push notifications
* Daily reminders
* Custom reminder times
* Missed-task notifications

### 4. XP and Leveling

Completing quests grants XP.

Example:

* Easy Quest = 25 XP
* Medium Quest = 50 XP
* Hard Quest = 100 XP

Users level up automatically when enough XP is earned.

### 5. Streak System

Consecutive completion of habits increases streaks.

Examples:

* 3-day streak
* 7-day streak
* 30-day streak
* 100-day streak

Higher streaks provide bonus XP and coins.

### 6. Achievement System

Unlock achievements such as:

* First Quest Completed
* Gym Warrior
* Study Master
* Early Bird
* Productivity Legend

### 7. Boss Battle Mode

Create virtual bosses representing bad habits.

Examples:

* Laziness Dragon
* Procrastination King
* Sleep Demon

Each completed quest damages the boss.

Example:

* Gym Quest = 50 Damage
* Study Quest = 40 Damage
* Reading Quest = 20 Damage

Defeating bosses grants rare rewards.

### 8. Daily Challenges

Generate random daily missions:

* Complete 3 quests
* Drink water 8 times
* Walk 5,000 steps

Rewards:

* Extra XP
* Coins
* Achievement progress

### 9. Statistics Dashboard

Show:

* Total XP earned
* Quests completed
* Weekly progress
* Monthly progress
* Habit consistency graphs
* Level history

### 10. Rewards Shop

Users spend coins on:

* Character skins
* Avatars
* Themes
* Pets
* Cosmetic upgrades

## UI Style

* Modern mobile design
* RPG-inspired visuals
* Dark mode by default
* Animated XP bar
* Achievement popups
* Smooth transitions
* Clean and intuitive navigation

## Technology Requirements

* Python
* Kivy for mobile UI
* SQLite database
* Local notifications
* Android support

## Architecture

Use a modular structure:

* Authentication
* Quest Management
* XP Engine
* Achievement Engine
* Notification Service
* Database Layer
* Statistics Module

## Goal

Create an engaging productivity app that motivates users to complete real-life tasks by making them feel like game quests. The app should be fun, rewarding, visually appealing, and encourage long-term habit formation through RPG mechanics.
### 11. Custom Task Creation

Users can create unlimited custom quests based on their personal goals and daily responsibilities.

Examples:

* Go to the Gym
* Complete Assignment
* Learn Python for 1 Hour
* Practice Guitar
* Read 20 Pages
* Walk the Dog
* Call Parents
* Clean Workspace
* Meditate for 10 Minutes
* Work on Side Project

Each custom task should allow:

* Task Title
* Description
* Category
* Difficulty Level
* XP Reward
* Coin Reward
* Due Date and Time
* Recurring Schedule (Daily, Weekly, Monthly)
* Reminder Notifications
* Custom Icons or Emojis

### Categories

Users can create or select categories such as:

* Fitness
* Study
* Work
* Health
* Personal Growth
* Finance
* Relationships
* Hobbies
* Custom Categories

### Dynamic Reward System

The app should automatically suggest rewards based on difficulty and estimated completion time.

Example:

* Easy Task → 20 XP, 10 Coins
* Medium Task → 50 XP, 25 Coins
* Hard Task → 100 XP, 50 Coins
* Epic Task → 250 XP, 100 Coins

Users can also manually customize rewards.

### Quest Chains

Users can combine multiple tasks into a larger mission.

Example:

Mission: Become Fit

* Go to Gym
* Drink 3L Water
* Walk 10,000 Steps
* Sleep Before 11 PM

Completing all sub-tasks grants a bonus reward.

### Smart Flexibility

The app should support both:

* Habit-based recurring quests
* One-time tasks

This allows users to manage daily habits, work assignments, university projects, personal goals, and long-term challenges in one place.

The system should be scalable so users can create hundreds of custom tasks without limitations.